# =============================================================================
# Jeffrey EventStreamingService — Manual gRPC Test Client
# =============================================================================

@host = localhost:443
@sessionId = 019d64e4-735e-791f-85a7-12e55e1cadb1

### 1. Minimal — drain existing events up to "now" and end
# Only the required fields. continuous defaults to false and no end_time
# is set, so the server uses clock.instant() as the cutoff. The stream
# delivers any buffered events from the streaming repository and then
# closes cleanly. Good baseline smoke test.
GRPC {{host}}/jeffrey.server.api.v1.EventStreamingService/SubscribeEvents
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sessionId": "{{sessionId}}",
  "eventTypes": ["jdk.CPULoad"],
  "startTime": 0
}

### 2. Live continuous with heartbeats
# Stays open indefinitely. sendEmptyBatches=true makes the server push an
# empty EventBatch every JFR flush cycle (~1s) so you can see the stream
# is alive even when no matching events arrive. Cancel from the Services
# tool window when done — server log should show
# "Client disconnected, closing subscriber stream" at INFO level.
GRPC {{host}}/jeffrey.server.api.v1.EventStreamingService/SubscribeEvents
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sessionId": "{{sessionId}}",
  "eventTypes": ["jdk.CPULoad", "jdk.GCHeapSummary", "jdk.ThreadStart", "jdk.ThreadEnd"],
  "continuous": true,
  "sendEmptyBatches": true
}


### 3. Historical replay — bounded time range
# Replays a fixed window from the streaming repository. Stream auto-stops
# once the latest delivered event timestamp reaches endTime. Replace the
# epoch-millis values below with a real window for your session.
GRPC {{host}}/jeffrey.server.api.v1.EventStreamingService/SubscribeEvents
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sessionId": "{{sessionId}}",
  "eventTypes": ["jdk.GCHeapSummary"],
  "startTime": 1759795200000,
  "endTime": 1759795260000,
  "continuous": false
}


### 4. Replay then live — catch-up plus tail
# startTime is set AND continuous=true. The server first replays everything
# from startTime out of the streaming repository, then keeps the stream
# open and tails new events as they arrive. endTime is ignored because
# continuous=true.
GRPC {{host}}/jeffrey.server.api.v1.EventStreamingService/SubscribeEvents
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sessionId": "{{sessionId}}",
  "eventTypes": ["jdk.ObjectAllocationSample"],
  "startTime": 1759795200000,
  "continuous": true,
  "sendEmptyBatches": true
}


### 5. Validation error — empty eventTypes (expect INVALID_ARGUMENT)
# Confirms server-side validation is wired up. Expected response is a gRPC
# error with status INVALID_ARGUMENT and message
# "At least one event type must be specified".
GRPC {{host}}/jeffrey.server.api.v1.EventStreamingService/SubscribeEvents
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sessionId": "{{sessionId}}",
  "eventTypes": []
}
